The paper focuses on content discovery in online communities, which involves social aspects (cs.SOC) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. The approach proposed also leverages passive observation of web-clicks, which falls under the category of web mining (cs.SI). The system is designed to be user-friendly and requires no active user engagement, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the security and privacy implications of the approach, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER).
